  "prompt": "How many of Quora answers are actually made-up stories or lies?",
  "response": "Determining the number of Quora answers that are made-up stories or lies is challenging as there is no definitive way to measure this accurately. Quora is a platform where people share their personal experiences and knowledge, but not every answer is fact-checked or verified. Thus, the community relies on the upvoting and commenting system to gauge the credibility of answers. While some users may intentionally or unintentionally provide false information, it's difficult to quantify the exact proportion. The best approach is to critically evaluate each answer, cross-reference with reliable sources, and consider the credibility of the user when consuming information on Quora.",
